This paper combines genetic algorithms with distributed computing, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses different partnering strategies for fitness evaluation, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of clusters and sub-populations also suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper examines the effects of these partnering strategies on optimization problems, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
